<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-25T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-25T21:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.516/627: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-26T09:00:00+07:00">June 26,
                                    1939—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>408. Department’s 113, June 23, 7 p.m. I took the occasion last evening
                            to bring this matter to attention of Kung who stated it was their desire
                            to cooperate with American banks and suggested that situation would be
                            simplified if American bankers joined Exchange <pb facs="0683" n="679" xml:id="pg_679"/> Stabilization Fund, from which they were buying
                            exchange. He pointed out that French had joined. It is my understanding
                            that one of the purposes of recent visit of French Ambassador to
                            Chungking was to complete an arrangement whereby a French contribution
                            to the Stabilization Fund set up by British was made.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping, Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>